        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 8:07PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 807 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sterlington, or 11 miles west of Bastrop, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Swartz, Sterlington, Fairbanks, Perryville, Guthrie, Deshard,
and Spencer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
